Hi teams,

I encountered a crash in rehist() and below is its backtrace. In frame 3, cleanup_sp is 0, which means it's already at the bottom of the cleanup_stack, but last_var cannot be found.

It seems like in rehist(), it invokes setexit() without updating cleanup_mark. If the program goes to error handling to reset the clean_stack[], it will clean more than required, which should be handled by cleanup_until() when the program jumps back to rehist().

I'm providing a patch below that might fix it. Feel free to apply it to the tcsh git, FreeBSD baseline, or fix it using other solutions. We can downstream it to our local and try it.

Thank you.

diff --git a/contrib/tcsh/sh.hist.c b/contrib/tcsh/sh.hist.c
index 14d862a3e7b..09f4814dbe3 100644
--- a/contrib/tcsh/sh.hist.c
+++ b/contrib/tcsh/sh.hist.c
@@ -1235,6 +1235,7 @@ rechist(Char *xfname, int ref)
     struct stat st;
     static Char *fname;
     static Char   *dumphist[] = {STRhistory, STRmhT, 0, 0};
+    size_t omark;

     if (fname == NULL && !ref)
        return;
@@ -1308,8 +1309,10 @@ rechist(Char *xfname, int ref)
 #endif
            }
            getexit(osetexit);
+           omark = cleanup_push_mark();
            if (setexit() == 0)
                loadhist(fname, 1);
+           cleanup_pop_mark(omark);
            resexit(osetexit);
        }
     }



